
******************************************************************************
svp<(file<,'force'><,'replace'><,'nodb'>)>-  Save Parameters
******************************************************************************
  
Saves parameters from current experiment to a file. The parameter set can be
retrieved with the rtp and rt macros. svp reflects any changes made in
parameters up to the moment of entering svp, including acquisition parameters
(unlike macro svf).

file is the name of the file, with the suffix .par added, to be created to save
the parameters. The default is the system prompts for a file name. You are
warned if you attempt to overwrite a parameter set that already exists.
If the 'force' option is given, you will not be warned.  The older parameter
set will be removed.
If the 'replace' option is given, only the parameters and text file in the
directory will be replaced. Any other files that may be in the .par directory
will be left alone.

'nodb' is a keyword to prevent the svp command from adding information to a
database.  This is useful if temporary parameter files are saved that will
soon be removed.
